-- Core Operational Schemas
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS scheduling;
COMMENT ON SCHEMA scheduling IS 'Core scheduling functionality: shifts, schedules, templates, and optimizations.
This schema contains all entities related to the creation, management, and execution of workforce schedules.
It includes tables for schedule templates, shift definitions, employee availability, and schedule assignments.
The schema supports complex scheduling requirements including union rules compliance, multi-location operations,
and advanced optimization algorithms. Critical for ensuring proper staffing levels while minimizing labor costs
and maximizing employee satisfaction. The schema is designed to handle high-volume scheduling operations with
performance optimizations for real-time schedule adjustments. Includes comprehensive audit capabilities to
track all schedule changes for compliance and accountability purposes.';

CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS hr;
COMMENT ON SCHEMA hr IS 'Human resources management: employees, skills, positions, and performance.
This schema contains all employee-related data including personal information, employment history, skills,
certifications, and performance metrics. It serves as the central repository for workforce capabilities
and qualifications that drive scheduling decisions. Includes comprehensive tracking of employee development
goals, training records, and career progression. Supports integration with performance management systems
to ensure scheduling decisions consider employee development needs. The schema includes robust security
controls to protect sensitive employee data while enabling appropriate access for scheduling managers.
Designed to support global workforce requirements with localization for different regions and compliance
with local labor regulations.';

CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS compliance;
COMMENT ON SCHEMA compliance IS 'Labor law compliance, rules, violations, and regulatory tracking.
This schema contains all entities related to regulatory compliance for workforce scheduling.
Includes tables for tracking labor laws by jurisdiction, union agreements, and company policies.
Supports automated compliance checking for schedules to prevent violations of labor regulations.
Tracks compliance violations and their resolution status for audit purposes.
Includes mechanisms for documenting compliance exceptions and approvals.
Critical for mitigating legal risks associated with improper scheduling practices.
The schema is designed to be easily extended to support new regulations as they emerge,
ensuring the system remains compliant with evolving labor laws across multiple jurisdictions.';

CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS operations;
COMMENT ON SCHEMA operations IS 'Business operations: locations, departments, business hours, tasks.
This schema contains all operational data necessary for workforce scheduling.
Includes definitions of business locations, departments, operational hours, and work tasks.
Supports hierarchical organization of business units for enterprise-wide scheduling.
Contains data about operational requirements that drive staffing needs, such as customer traffic patterns
and service level requirements. Enables scheduling based on operational forecasts and historical demand patterns.
The schema is designed to integrate with operational systems to automatically adjust schedules based on
real-time business conditions. Critical for ensuring schedules align with actual business needs rather than
just labor availability.';

CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS analytics;
COMMENT ON SCHEMA analytics IS 'Business intelligence: forecasting, metrics, KPIs, and reporting data.
This schema contains all data structures for workforce analytics and business intelligence.
Includes tables for storing historical scheduling data, performance metrics, and forecasting models.
Supports advanced analytics capabilities including predictive scheduling and optimization.
Contains pre-aggregated data for rapid reporting and dashboarding.
Enables tracking of key workforce metrics over time to identify trends and opportunities for improvement.
The schema is optimized for analytical queries with appropriate indexing and partitioning strategies.
Critical for data-driven decision making in workforce management, providing insights that help optimize
staffing levels, reduce labor costs, and improve employee satisfaction.';

CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS finance;
COMMENT ON SCHEMA finance IS 'Financial management: labor costs, budgets, payroll, and cost analysis.
This schema contains all financial data related to workforce scheduling.
Includes tables for tracking labor costs by position, department, and location.
Supports budgeting and forecasting of labor expenses.
Enables cost analysis of different scheduling scenarios to identify optimal staffing levels.
Integrates with payroll systems to ensure accurate compensation for scheduled work.
Contains historical cost data for trend analysis and predictive modeling.
Critical for controlling labor costs while maintaining appropriate staffing levels.
The schema is designed to support complex cost calculations including overtime, premium pay,
and benefit allocations. Essential for financial accountability in workforce management decisions.';

