-- Serial No: 20 | TABLE: scheduling.schedule_compliance
-- Description: Compliance validation results for schedules
-- Business Case: The schedule_compliance table stores the results of compliance checks performed on schedules
-- to ensure adherence to labor laws, union agreements, and company policies. This information is critical
-- for mitigating legal and financial risks associated with improper scheduling practices. The table captures
-- detailed information about each compliance rule evaluated, including the specific violations found, their
-- severity, and potential remediation options. It supports historical tracking of compliance status to
-- identify recurring issues and measure improvement over time. The design accommodates different compliance
-- frameworks for various jurisdictions and business units. The table also tracks the review and resolution
-- status of compliance issues to support proper documentation and accountability. This information is
-- valuable for compliance reporting and audit preparation. The data structure is optimized for rapid
-- querying during schedule validation and for generating compliance dashboards that highlight potential
-- risk areas. The table is essential for maintaining defensible scheduling practices and demonstrating
-- due diligence in compliance matters.
