-- Partial index for active schedules
-- Serial No: 23 | INDEX: idx_schedules_active
-- Purpose: Optimizes queries for currently active schedules
-- Business Case: This partial index focuses exclusively on active schedules, which represent the small
-- subset of schedules that are relevant for current operations (typically those covering the current
-- and upcoming time periods). By excluding historical and archived schedules, the index remains small
-- and highly efficient for the most common operational queries. Most scheduling operations - including
-- schedule creation, modification, and employee self-service features - primarily interact with active
-- schedules. The partial index provides significant performance benefits for these operations while
-- minimizing storage overhead and maintenance costs. It also supports proper data lifecycle management
-- by separating operational data from historical archives. The index is particularly valuable for
-- organizations with long schedule histories, where the ratio of active to historical schedules can
-- be very small. This targeted indexing strategy ensures that day-to-day operations remain responsive
-- regardless of historical data volume.
-- KPI: Active schedule query performance, User interface responsiveness,
--      Schedule modification speed, Operational query throughput,
--      Index maintenance overhead
-- Feature Reference: 111, 112, 113, 114, 115
