-- BRIN index for time-series data
-- Serial No: 24 | INDEX: idx_forecasted_demand_date
-- Purpose: Optimizes range queries on forecasted demand dates
-- Business Case: This BRIN (Block Range INdex) index is specifically designed for time-series data
-- like forecasted demand, where values are naturally ordered by time. It provides excellent performance
-- for range queries on large datasets while consuming significantly less storage space than traditional
-- B-tree indexes. The index works by storing summary information about ranges of pages in the table,
-- making it highly efficient for queries that filter by date ranges - the most common access pattern
-- for demand forecast data. It is particularly valuable for historical analysis and reporting queries
-- that span extended time periods. The BRIN index structure also has lower maintenance overhead for
-- bulk data loading operations, which is important for forecast data that is frequently updated in
-- large batches. This indexing strategy ensures that demand-based scheduling operations remain efficient
-- even as historical data accumulates over time.
-- KPI: Historical query performance, Forecast data loading speed,
