    -- dimensions of data quality including completeness, accuracy, consistency, timeliness,
    -- and validity. It is critical for building comprehensive data quality scorecards that
    -- track progress against organizational data quality goals. The metric types are
    -- designed to cover common data quality assessment methodologies while allowing for
    -- future expansion as new measurement approaches emerge. This ensures the system
    -- remains adaptable to evolving data quality practices and regulatory requirements.
    -- The enumeration also supports integration with industry-standard data quality
    -- frameworks by mapping to common metric definitions. By providing this standardization,
