impact profiles. Includes details about expected attendance, duration, proximity, and historical impact data. Includes
mechanisms for event impact scoring. Historical event data maintained for predictive modeling. Tracks event status changes
for timely adjustments. Supports varying event impacts across different locations. Accommodates regularly scheduled and
one-time events. Centralizes event information for consistent handling of event-based scheduling. Optimized for rapid
querying during schedule creation.';

        -- Serial No: 79 | TABLE: reporting.report_configurations
        -- Description: Configuration and metadata for analytical reports
        -- Business Case: The report_configurations table stores metadata and configuration details for all analytical reports
        -- within the workforce scheduling system, providing a centralized repository for report definitions. It captures
        -- essential information including report purpose, data sources, parameters, and visualization settings to ensure
        -- consistent report generation across the organization. The table supports versioning of report definitions to
        -- track changes over time and maintain historical reporting standards. Each configuration includes security
        -- controls to ensure reports only access data the user is authorized to see, maintaining data governance
        -- throughout the reporting process. Comprehensive usage statistics are tracked to identify popular reports
        -- and underutilized configurations that may be candidates for deprecation. The implementation includes
        -- performance metrics to monitor report execution times and optimize slow-performing reports. For scheduled
        -- reports, the system stores scheduling parameters to enable automated report generation and delivery.
        -- The table also tracks user preferences for report format and delivery method to enhance user experience.
        -- By centralizing report configurations, the system reduces the time and effort required to create new
        -- reports while ensuring consistency in data presentation and analysis. The design accommodates both
        -- operational reports needed for daily management and strategic reports for executive decision making.
        -- The table is optimized for rapid lookup during report execution and for historical analysis of report
        -- usage patterns, supporting continuous improvement of the reporting ecosystem.
        -- KPI: Report configuration completeness, Report generation time,
        --      Report usage rate, Configuration compliance rate,
        --      Report error resolution time
        -- Feature Reference: 411, 412, 413, 414, 415
        CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS reporting.report_configurations (
            report_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
            report_code VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL CHECK (report_code ~ '^[A-Z0-9_]{3,50}$'),
            name VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL,
            description TEXT,
            report_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL CHECK (report_type IN ('STANDARD', 'AD_HOC', 'DASHBOARD', 'REGULATORY', 'EXECUTIVE')),
            category VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL CHECK (category IN ('SCHEDULING', 'ATTENDANCE', 'COMPLIANCE', 'PRODUCTIVITY', 'LABOR_COST', 'FORECASTING')),
            data_sources VARCHAR(200)[] NOT NULL,
            parameters JSONB DEFAULT '[]'::JSONB,
            visualization_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL CHECK (visualization_type IN ('TABLE', 'BAR_CHART', 'LINE_CHART', 'PIE_CHART', 'HEATMAP', 'GAUGE', 'MAP')),
            default_filters JSONB,
            column_configuration JSONB,
            refresh_frequency VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'ON_DEMAND'
                CHECK (refresh_frequency IN ('REALTIME', 'HOURLY', 'DAILY', 'WEEKLY', 'MONTHLY', 'ON_DEMAND')),
            version_number VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1.0',
            approval_status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'DRAFT'
                CHECK (approval_status IN ('DRAFT', 'REVIEW', 'APPROVED', 'REJECTED', 'DEPRECATED')),
            approved_by UUID REFERENCES hr.employees(employee_id),
            approved_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE,
            is_active BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT TRUE,
            created_by UUID NOT NULL,
            updated_by UUID,
            created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
            updated_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
            metadata JSONB
        );

        -- Add indexes for performance
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_report_configurations_active ON reporting.report_configurations(is_active) WHERE is_active = TRUE;
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_report_configurations_type ON reporting.report_configurations(report_type);
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_report_configurations_parameters ON reporting.report_configurations USING GIN(parameters);
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_report_configurations_filters ON reporting.report_configurations USING GIN(default_filters);
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_report_configurations_metadata ON reporting.report_configurations USING GIN(metadata);

        -- Add triggers for audit columns
        CREATE TRIGGER trg_report_configurations_updated_at
        BEFORE UPDATE ON reporting.report_configurations
        FOR EACH ROW
        EXECUTE FUNCTION update_updated_at_column();

        COMMENT ON TABLE reporting.report_configurations IS 'Configuration and metadata for analytical reports.
        Stores metadata and configuration details for all analytical reports within the workforce scheduling system. Captures report
        purpose, data sources, parameters, and visualization settings. Supports versioning of report definitions. Includes security
        controls to ensure reports access only authorized data. Tracks usage statistics to identify popular reports. Includes
        performance metrics to monitor execution times. Stores scheduling parameters for automated report generation. Tracks user
        preferences for format and delivery method. Reduces time and effort required to create new reports. Accommodates both
        operational and strategic reports. Optimized for rapid lookup during report execution and historical analysis.';

        -- Serial No: 80 | TABLE: scheduling.shift_preferences
        -- Description: Employee shift preferences and constraints for optimized scheduling
        -- Business Case: The shift_preferences table captures employee preferences and constraints for shift scheduling,
        -- enabling the creation of schedules that maximize employee satisfaction while meeting business needs. It records
        -- both recurring patterns (e.g., "available only on weekends") and specific date exceptions (e.g., "unavailable
        -- July 4th"), providing a comprehensive view of employee availability preferences. The table supports multiple
        -- preference types including preferred shifts, days to avoid, and availability windows, allowing for nuanced
        -- scheduling decisions. Each preference includes metadata about its priority, effective dates, and approval
        -- status to support proper workflow handling. The implementation accommodates complex preference scenarios
        -- such as split availability windows and partial-day preferences. Preference data is versioned to track
        -- changes over time, which is important for understanding historical scheduling patterns and resolving
        -- disputes. The table is optimized for rapid querying during schedule generation, which involves evaluating
        -- preference constraints for potentially hundreds of employees simultaneously. Historical preference data
        -- is used to identify patterns and improve the scheduling algorithm's ability to predict employee preferences.
        -- For compliance purposes, the system tracks the approval status of preferences that may conflict with
        -- business requirements or labor regulations. By centralizing preference management, the system enables
        -- more effective communication between employees and managers about scheduling expectations while
        -- providing the data needed for optimization algorithms to create schedules that balance business and
        -- employee needs.
        -- KPI: Preference fulfillment rate, Schedule satisfaction score,
        --      Preference update frequency, Preference data completeness,
        --      Scheduling conflict rate
        -- Feature Reference: 416, 417, 418, 419, 420
        CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS scheduling.shift_preferences (
            preference_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
            employee_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES hr.employees(employee_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
            preference_type scheduling.availability_type_enum NOT NULL DEFAULT 'PREFERRED',
            start_date DATE NOT NULL,
            end_date DATE,
            day_of_week INTEGER CHECK (day_of_week BETWEEN 1 AND 7),
            start_time TIME NOT NULL,
            end_time TIME NOT NULL CHECK (end_time > start_time),
            is_recurring BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
            recurrence_pattern VARCHAR(50),
            recurrence_interval INTEGER,
            recurrence_end_date DATE,
            specific_date DATE,
            priority INTEGER DEFAULT 0 CHECK (priority BETWEEN -10 AND 10),
            is_approved BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
            approval_notes TEXT,
            approved_by UUID REFERENCES hr.employees(employee_id),
            approval_date TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE,
            source_system VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'EMPLOYEE_SELF_SERVICE'
                CHECK (source_system IN ('EMPLOYEE_SELF_SERVICE', 'MANAGER', 'HR_SYSTEM', 'IMPORTED')),
            notes TEXT,
            version INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1 CHECK (version >= 1),
            created_by UUID NOT NULL,
            updated_by UUID,
            created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
            updated_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
            metadata JSONB
        );

        -- Add indexes for performance
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_shift_preferences_employee ON scheduling.shift_preferences(employee_id);
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_shift_preferences_type ON scheduling.shift_preferences(preference_type);
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_shift_preferences_dates ON scheduling.shift_preferences(start_date, end_date);
