            Accommodates different analysis methodologies. Centralizes attendance pattern data for consistent evaluation. Optimized for
            rapid querying during scheduling optimization.';

            -- Serial No: 113 | TABLE: compliance.union_agreements
            -- Description: Collective bargaining agreements and union contracts
            -- Business Case: The union_agreements table serves as the central repository for all collective bargaining
            -- agreements and union contracts applicable to the organization's workforce. It captures detailed provisions
            -- around working hours, overtime, rest periods, seniority rules, and other employment conditions mandated
            -- by union contracts. The table supports hierarchical organization of agreements from national to local
            -- levels, ensuring proper application of the most specific applicable agreement. Each agreement includes
            -- metadata about its effective dates, covered employee groups, and enforcement priority to support
            -- appropriate implementation in scheduling systems. The design accommodates complex agreement structures
            -- through a combination of standard rule types and custom expression capabilities, enabling precise
            -- representation of nuanced contractual requirements. Historical versions of agreements are maintained
            -- to support compliance verification for past scheduling decisions. The table also tracks agreement
            -- updates and implementation deadlines to ensure timely adaptation of scheduling practices. For
            -- multinational organizations, the system supports translation of agreements into multiple languages
            -- while maintaining the legal accuracy of requirements. By centralizing union agreement information,
            -- the organization can ensure consistent compliance across all locations while reducing the risk of
            -- labor disputes due to misinterpreted contractual terms. The table is optimized for rapid querying
            -- during compliance checks, which is critical for real-time scheduling validation and preventing
            -- contractual violations before schedules are published.
            -- KPI: Contract compliance rate, Agreement update implementation time,
            --      Compliance violation resolution time, Agreement coverage completeness,
            --      Audit success rate
            -- Feature Reference: 581, 582, 583, 584, 585
            CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS compliance.union_agreements (
                agreement_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
