                -- setting and performance evaluation. Each benchmark configuration includes metadata about its
                -- effective dates, priority, and approval status to support proper workflow handling. The
                -- implementation accommodates complex benchmark scenarios such as conditional benchmarks that
                -- apply only under specific business conditions. Benchmark data is versioned to track changes
                -- over time, which is important for understanding historical performance against evolving goals.
                -- The table is optimized for rapid querying during performance evaluation, which involves comparing
                -- actual performance against configured benchmarks for potentially hundreds of metrics simultaneously.
                -- Historical benchmark data is used to identify patterns and improve the goal-setting process. For
                -- compliance purposes, the system tracks the approval status of benchmarks that may conflict with
                -- business requirements or regulatory standards. By centralizing benchmark configuration, the system
                -- enables more effective communication between leadership and operational teams about performance
                -- expectations while providing the data needed for performance management systems. The table is
                -- optimized for rapid querying during performance evaluation, which is critical for timely feedback
                -- on scheduling effectiveness.
                -- KPI: Benchmark configuration completeness, Performance goal achievement rate,
                --      Benchmark update frequency, Benchmark data completeness,
                --      Performance gap closure rate
