                -- tracks key creation, usage, and revocation to support security investigations and compliance reporting.
                -- The implementation includes mechanisms for key rotation and revocation to enhance security posture
                -- and respond to potential breaches. Key usage patterns are monitored to detect anomalous behavior
                -- that may indicate compromised keys. The design accommodates high-volume key operations while
                -- maintaining performance for authentication-critical paths. For sensitive operations, the system
                -- supports short-lived keys with limited scope to minimize potential damage from key compromise. The
                -- table also tracks client information to support device-based authentication policies and to provide
                -- context for security alerts. By centralizing key management, the system ensures consistent security
                -- practices across all authentication mechanisms while providing the flexibility needed for different
                -- integration scenarios. The table is optimized for rapid lookup during authentication operations,
                -- which are critical for system performance and security.
