                -- critical for diagnosing delivery failures, optimizing communication performance, and ensuring
                -- timely delivery of critical notifications. The table supports multiple delivery channels including
                -- email, SMS, and in-app notifications, accommodating different communication methods. Each delivery
                -- record includes metadata about the message type, recipient, and delivery context to enable accurate
                -- assessment of delivery outcomes. Historical delivery data is maintained to identify patterns in
                -- delivery success and measure the impact of configuration changes over time. For operational
                -- efficiency, the system tracks retry attempts to avoid redundant processing and enable targeted
                -- troubleshooting. The table integrates with the message queue system to enable real-time monitoring
                -- of delivery status and automated retry processing. The design accommodates complex delivery
                -- scenarios with multiple retry attempts and varying response patterns, providing detailed insights
                -- into communication behavior. By centralizing delivery tracking, the organization can ensure
                -- consistent evaluation of communication performance while providing the data needed for continuous
                -- improvement. The table is optimized for rapid querying during incident response, which often
                -- involves identifying delivery issues across multiple channels and time periods.
