                -- Serial No: 189 | TABLE: data_governance.data_quality_communication_metrics
                -- Description: Historical metrics for data quality communication effectiveness
                -- Business Case: The data_quality_communication_metrics table stores historical metrics for
                -- measuring the effectiveness of data quality communications across the organization. It captures
                -- key engagement indicators such as open rates, click-through rates, and response rates to
                -- support ongoing assessment of communication effectiveness. This information is critical for
                -- identifying communication issues before they impact data quality awareness and behavior. The
                -- table supports multiple metric types including channel-specific metrics and audience-segment
                -- metrics, enabling holistic assessment of communication health. Historical metric data is
                -- versioned to track changes over time and measure improvement against communication goals. Each
                -- metric record includes metadata about the calculation method, execution frequency, and target
                -- values to support data quality communication goal setting and monitoring. The implementation
                -- includes mechanisms for automated metric calculation through scheduled jobs, ensuring timely
                -- assessment of communication effectiveness. For metrics with defined targets, the table stores
                -- variance calculations to highlight areas requiring attention. Historical metric data is used
                -- to establish baselines and detect anomalies that may indicate underlying communication issues.
                -- By centralizing communication metrics, the system enables comprehensive data quality
                -- communication dashboards that provide visibility into communication health across the
                -- organization. The table is optimized for time-series analysis of communication metrics,
                -- supporting trend identification and predictive communication management.
