                -- objectives, target audience, timeline, and budget to support comprehensive campaign
                -- management. The table supports multiple campaign types including awareness campaigns,
                -- behavior change campaigns, and policy rollout campaigns, accommodating different
                -- communication needs. Each campaign record includes metadata about the campaign owner, status,
                -- and key performance indicators to enable proper governance of communication activities. The
                -- implementation includes robust tracking of campaign milestones and deliverables to ensure
                -- timely execution of communication activities. Historical campaign data is maintained to
                -- identify patterns in campaign effectiveness and measure the impact of communication strategies
                -- over time. For operational efficiency, the system tracks campaign ROI to enable measurement
                -- of communication effectiveness and justify future communication investments. The table
                -- integrates with the marketing automation system to enable end-to-end tracking of campaign
                -- activities from planning through execution and measurement. The design accommodates complex
                -- campaign scenarios with multiple phases, channels, and audience segments, providing detailed
                -- insights into campaign effectiveness. By centralizing campaign management, the organization
                -- can ensure consistent execution of communication activities while providing the data needed
                -- for continuous improvement of communication strategies. The table is optimized for rapid
                -- querying during campaign planning and execution, which is critical for timely adjustments to
                -- communication activities.
                -- KPI: Campaign completion rate, Campaign ROI,
                --      Campaign effectiveness score, Campaign delivery timeliness,
                --      Campaign data quality score
                -- Feature Reference: 976, 977, 978, 979, 980
                CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS data_governance.data_quality_communication_campaigns (
                    campaign_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
                    campaign_code VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL CHECK (campaign_code ~ '^[A-Z0-9_]{3,50}$'),
                    name VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL,
                    description TEXT,
                    campaign_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL CHECK (campaign_type IN ('AWARENESS', 'BEHAVIOR_CHANGE', 'POLICY_ROLLOUT',
                        'TRAINING_PROMOTION', 'SUCCESS_STORY', 'RECOGNITION')),
