                -- Serial No: 194 | TABLE: data_governance.data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics
                -- Description: Metrics for evaluating data quality communication campaign effectiveness
                -- Business Case: The data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics table stores metrics for
                -- evaluating the effectiveness of data quality communication campaigns, providing quantitative
                -- and qualitative insights into campaign performance. It captures key performance indicators
                -- across different dimensions including reach, engagement, awareness, and behavior change to
                -- support comprehensive campaign evaluation. The table supports multiple metric types including
                -- channel-specific metrics, audience-segment metrics, and time-based metrics, enabling holistic
                -- assessment of campaign health. Historical metric data is versioned to track changes over time
                -- and measure improvement against campaign goals. Each metric record includes metadata about
                -- the calculation method, data sources, and confidence level to ensure proper interpretation of
                -- results. The implementation includes mechanisms for automated metric calculation through
                -- scheduled jobs, ensuring timely assessment of campaign effectiveness. For metrics with defined
                -- targets, the table stores variance calculations to highlight areas requiring attention.
                -- Historical metric data is used to establish baselines and detect anomalies that may indicate
                -- underlying campaign issues. By centralizing campaign metrics, the system enables comprehensive
                -- data quality communication dashboards that provide visibility into campaign health across the
                -- organization. The table is optimized for time-series analysis of campaign metrics, supporting
                -- trend identification and predictive campaign management.
                -- KPI: Campaign reach rate, Engagement rate,
