                        Captures structured feedback from employees regarding data quality communications. Provides insights for communication policy
                        improvements. Supports multiple feedback methodologies including periodic and pulse surveys. Includes metadata about timing
                        and context for meaningful analysis. Includes validation rules to detect response bias. Historical data maintained for trend
                        tracking. Tracks anonymity status and privacy controls for compliance. Integrates with communication system to correlate feedback
                        with specific communications. Accommodates both quantitative ratings and qualitative comments. Centralizes feedback data for
                        consistent analysis. Optimized for rapid querying during satisfaction analysis.';

                        -- Serial No: 242 | TABLE: system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns
                        -- Description: Management of data quality communication campaigns for import processes
                        -- Business Case: The import_data_quality_communication_campaigns table manages data quality
                        -- communication campaigns related to import processes across the organization, providing
                        -- visibility into campaign planning, execution, and effectiveness. It captures detailed
                        -- information about each campaign including objectives, target audience, timeline, and budget
                        -- to support comprehensive campaign management. The table supports multiple campaign types
                        -- including awareness campaigns, behavior change campaigns, and policy rollout campaigns,
                        -- accommodating different communication needs. Each campaign record includes metadata about the
                        -- campaign owner, status, and key performance indicators to enable proper governance of
                        -- communication activities. The implementation includes robust tracking of campaign milestones
                        -- and deliverables to ensure timely execution of communication activities. Historical campaign
                        -- data is maintained to identify patterns in campaign effectiveness and measure the impact of
                        -- communication strategies over time. For operational efficiency, the system tracks campaign
                        -- ROI to enable measurement of communication effectiveness and justify future communication
                        -- investments. The table integrates with the marketing automation system to enable end-to-end
                        -- tracking of campaign activities from planning through execution and measurement. The design
                        -- accommodates complex campaign scenarios with multiple phases, channels, and audience
                        -- segments, providing detailed insights into campaign effectiveness. By centralizing campaign
                        -- management, the organization can ensure consistent execution of communication activities
                        -- while providing the data needed for continuous improvement of communication strategies. The
                        -- table is optimized for rapid querying during campaign planning and execution, which is
                        -- critical for timely adjustments to communication activities.
                        -- KPI: Campaign completion rate, Campaign ROI,
                        --      Campaign effectiveness score, Campaign delivery timeliness,
                        --      Campaign data quality score
                        -- Feature Reference: 1226, 1227, 1228, 1229, 1230
                        CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns (
                            campaign_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
                            campaign_code VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL CHECK (campaign_code ~ '^[A-Z0-9_]{3,50}$'),
                            name VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL,
                            description TEXT,
                            campaign_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL CHECK (campaign_type IN ('AWARENESS', 'BEHAVIOR_CHANGE', 'POLICY_ROLLOUT',
                                'TRAINING_PROMOTION', 'SUCCESS_STORY', 'RECOGNITION')),
                            start_date DATE NOT NULL,
                            end_date DATE NOT NULL CHECK (end_date >= start_date),
                            owner_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES hr.employees(employee_id),
                            status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'PLANNING'
                                CHECK (status IN ('PLANNING', 'EXECUTING', 'COMPLETED', 'CANCELLED', 'ON_HOLD')),
                            budget NUMERIC(12,2) CHECK (budget >= 0.00),
                            actual_spend NUMERIC(12,2) DEFAULT 0.00 CHECK (actual_spend >= 0.00),
                            kpis JSONB NOT NULL,
                            target_audience JSONB NOT NULL,
                            channels JSONB NOT NULL,
                            campaign_assets JSONB,
                            milestones JSONB,
                            success_metrics JSONB,
                            lessons_learned TEXT,
                            created_by UUID NOT NULL,
                            updated_by UUID,
                            created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
                            updated_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
                            metadata JSONB
                        );

                        -- Add indexes for performance
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaigns_type ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns(campaign_type);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaigns_owner ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns(owner_id);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaigns_status ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns(status);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaigns_dates ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns(start_date, end_date);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaigns_audience ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns
                            USING GIN(target_audience);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaigns_channels ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns
                            USING GIN(channels);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaigns_kpis ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns
                            USING GIN(kpis);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaigns_metadata ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns
                            USING GIN(metadata);

                        -- Add triggers for audit columns
                        CREATE TRIGGER trg_import_data_quality_communication_campaigns_updated_at
                        BEFORE UPDATE ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns
                        FOR EACH ROW
                        EXECUTE FUNCTION update_updated_at_column();

                        COMMENT ON TABLE system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns IS 'Management of data quality communication campaigns for import processes.
                        Manages data quality communication campaigns across the organization. Captures campaign planning, execution, and effectiveness.
                        Supports multiple campaign types including awareness and behavior change campaigns. Includes metadata about campaign owner
                        and status. Tracks campaign milestones and deliverables for timely execution. Historical data maintained to identify campaign
                        effectiveness patterns. Tracks campaign ROI for effectiveness measurement. Integrates with marketing automation system for
                        end-to-end tracking. Accommodates complex campaign scenarios with multiple phases. Centralizes campaign management for
                        consistent execution. Optimized for rapid querying during campaign planning and execution.';

                        -- Serial No: 243 | TABLE: system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities
                        -- Description: Tracking of activities within data quality communication campaigns for import processes
                        -- Business Case: The import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities table captures
                        -- detailed information about activities within data quality communication campaigns related to
                        -- import processes, providing visibility into campaign execution at the granular level. It
                        -- records each activity with comprehensive context including timing, resources, and outcomes to
                        -- support campaign management and evaluation. The table supports multiple activity types
                        -- including content creation, channel deployment, and event execution, accommodating different
                        -- campaign execution workflows. Each activity record includes metadata about the activity owner,
                        -- status, and dependencies to enable proper workflow management. Historical activity data is
                        -- maintained to identify patterns in activity effectiveness and measure the impact of execution
                        -- changes over time. For operational efficiency, the system tracks activity duration and
                        -- resource utilization to enable measurement of execution efficiency. The table integrates with
                        -- the project management system to enable comprehensive tracking of campaign activities from
                        -- planning through execution and measurement. The design accommodates complex activity
                        -- scenarios with dependencies between activities and conditional execution paths, providing
                        -- detailed insights into campaign execution effectiveness. By centralizing activity tracking,
                        -- the organization can ensure consistent evaluation of campaign execution while providing the
                        -- flexibility needed for different campaign contexts. The table is optimized for rapid querying
                        -- during campaign execution, which often involves identifying bottlenecks across multiple
                        -- activity instances.
                        -- KPI: Activity completion rate, Activity timeliness,
                        --      Resource utilization efficiency, Activity effectiveness score,
                        --      Campaign execution efficiency
                        -- Feature Reference: 1231, 1232, 1233, 1234, 1235
                        CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities (
                            activity_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
                            campaign_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns(campaign_id),
                            activity_code VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL CHECK (activity_code ~ '^[A-Z0-9_]{3,50}$'),
                            name VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL,
                            description TEXT,
                            activity_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL CHECK (activity_type IN ('CONTENT_CREATION', 'CHANNEL_DEPLOYMENT', 'EVENT_EXECUTION',
                                'METRICS_COLLECTION', 'ANALYSIS', 'REPORTING')),
                            owner_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES hr.employees(employee_id),
                            status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'PLANNED'
                                CHECK (status IN ('PLANNED', 'IN_PROGRESS', 'COMPLETED', 'CANCELLED', 'DELAYED')),
                            planned_start_date DATE NOT NULL,
                            planned_end_date DATE NOT NULL CHECK (planned_end_date >= planned_start_date),
                            actual_start_date DATE,
                            actual_end_date DATE,
                            duration_planned INTERVAL,
                            duration_actual INTERVAL,
                            dependencies UUID[],
                            required_resources JSONB,
                            outcomes JSONB,
                            metrics JSONB,
                            created_by UUID NOT NULL,
                            updated_by UUID,
                            created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
                            updated_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
                            metadata JSONB
                        );

                        -- Add indexes for performance
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities_campaign ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities(campaign_id);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities_type ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities(activity_type);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities_owner ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities(owner_id);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities_status ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities(status);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities_planned ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities(planned_start_date, planned_end_date);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities_actual ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities(actual_start_date, actual_end_date);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities_dependencies ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities
                            USING GIN(dependencies);
                        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities_metadata ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities
                            USING GIN(metadata);

                        -- Add triggers for audit columns
                        CREATE TRIGGER trg_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities_updated_at
                        BEFORE UPDATE ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities
                        FOR EACH ROW
                        EXECUTE FUNCTION update_updated_at_column();

                        COMMENT ON TABLE system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities IS 'Tracking of activities within data quality communication campaigns for import processes.
                        Captures detailed information about activities within communication campaigns. Records each activity with comprehensive context.
                        Supports multiple activity types including content creation and channel deployment. Includes metadata about activity owner and
                        status. Historical data maintained to identify activity effectiveness patterns. Tracks activity duration and resource utilization.
                        Integrates with project management system for comprehensive tracking. Accommodates complex activity scenarios with dependencies.
                        Centralizes activity tracking for consistent evaluation. Optimized for rapid querying during campaign execution.';

                        -- Serial No: 244 | TABLE: system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics
-- Description: Metrics for evaluating data quality communication campaign effectiveness for import processes
-- Business Case: The import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics table stores metrics
-- for evaluating the effectiveness of data quality communication campaigns related to import
-- processes, providing quantitative and qualitative insights into campaign performance. It
-- captures key performance indicators across different dimensions including reach, engagement,
-- awareness, and behavior change to support comprehensive campaign evaluation. The table
-- supports multiple metric types including channel-specific metrics, audience-segment metrics,
-- and time-based metrics, enabling holistic assessment of campaign health. Historical metric
-- data is versioned to track changes over time and measure improvement against campaign goals.
-- Each metric record includes metadata about the calculation method, data sources, and
-- confidence level to ensure proper interpretation of results. The implementation includes
-- mechanisms for automated metric calculation through scheduled jobs, ensuring timely
-- assessment of campaign effectiveness. For metrics with defined targets, the table stores
-- variance calculations to highlight areas requiring attention. Historical metric data is used
-- to establish baselines and detect anomalies that may indicate underlying campaign issues. By
-- centralizing campaign metrics, the system enables comprehensive data quality communication
-- dashboards that provide visibility into campaign health across the organization. The table is
-- optimized for time-series analysis of campaign metrics, supporting trend identification and
-- predictive campaign management.
-- KPI: Campaign reach rate, Engagement rate,
--      Awareness improvement rate, Campaign ROI,
--      Behavior change rate
-- Feature Reference: 1236, 1237, 1238, 1239, 1240
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics (
    metric_id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT uuid_generate_v4(),
    campaign_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES system.import_data_quality_communication_campaigns(campaign_id),
    activity_id UUID REFERENCES system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_activities(activity_id),
    metric_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL CHECK (metric_type IN ('REACH', 'ENGAGEMENT', 'AWARENESS', 'BEHAVIOR_CHANGE', 'ROI')),
    metric_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    calculation_method VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL CHECK (calculation_method IN ('AUTOMATED', 'MANUAL_ENTRY',
        'SURVEY', 'OBSERVATION')),
    calculation_time TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    metric_value NUMERIC(10,2) NOT NULL,
    metric_unit VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    target_value NUMERIC(10,2),
    warning_threshold NUMERIC(10,2),
    failure_threshold NUMERIC(10,2),
    audience_segment JSONB,
    channel VARCHAR(50),
    time_period VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL CHECK (time_period IN ('DAILY', 'WEEKLY', 'MONTHLY', 'CAMPAIGN')),
    context JSONB,
    data_quality_score NUMERIC(5,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 1.00 CHECK (data_quality_score BETWEEN 0.00 AND 1.00),
    created_by UUID NOT NULL,
    updated_by UUID,
    created_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    metadata JSONB
);

-- Add indexes for performance
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics_campaign ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics(campaign_id);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics_activity ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics(activity_id)
    WHERE activity_id IS NOT NULL;
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics_type ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics(metric_type);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics_name ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics(metric_name);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics_time ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics(calculation_time DESC);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics_value ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics(metric_value);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics_segment ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics
    USING GIN(audience_segment);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics_channel ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics(channel);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics_period ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics(time_period);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics_metadata ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics
    USING GIN(metadata);

-- Add triggers for audit columns
CREATE TRIGGER trg_import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics_updated_at
BEFORE UPDATE ON system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics
FOR EACH ROW
EXECUTE FUNCTION update_updated_at_column();

COMMENT ON TABLE system.import_data_quality_communication_campaign_metrics IS 'Metrics for evaluating data quality communication campaign effectiveness for import processes.
Stores metrics for evaluating communication campaign effectiveness. Captures key performance indicators across different
dimensions. Supports multiple metric types including channel-specific and audience-segment metrics. Historical data versioned
to track changes over time. Includes metadata about calculation method and data sources. Includes mechanisms for automated
metric calculation. Stores variance calculations for metrics with defined targets. Used to establish baselines and detect
anomalies. Centralizes campaign metrics for comprehensive dashboards. Optimized for time-series analysis of campaign metrics.';




